util::id_set::AtomicIdSet::<I>::load.doc:
Loads the value of the set with the given ordering.

 This operation is not atomic. When racing with a [`Self::store`]
 operation, this load may return a set that contains a portion of the
 new value and a portion of the old value. Load on each specific
 word is atomic, and follows the specified ordering.

 Note that load with [`Ordering::Release`] is a valid operation, which
 is different from the normal atomic operations. When coupled with
 [`Ordering::Release`], it actually performs `fetch_or(0, Release)`.

smp::IpiSender::inter_processor_call.doc:
Executes a function on other processors.

 See [`inter_processor_call`] for details. The purpose of exporting this
 method is to enable callers to check whether [`IPI_SENDER`] has been
 initialized.

cpu::local::CpuLocal::<T, S>::get_on_cpu.doc:
Gets access to the CPU-local value on a specific CPU.

 This allows the caller to access CPU-local data from a remote CPU,
 so the data type must be `Sync`.

doc:
Dispatches all the pending TLB flush requests.

 All previous pending requests issued by [`Self::issue_tlb_flush`] or
 [`Self::issue_tlb_flush_with`] starts to be processed after this
 function. But it may not be synchronous. Upon the return of this
 function, the TLB entries may not be coherent.
